Quick note
Use this as a mock-interview sheet. I’ve included straightforward factual questions, scenario questions (“what would you do if…?”), and behavioral/ownership questions that show you understand the WHY (not just the how).

A. General / Definitions
Q: What are the three release frequencies at CureMD?
A: Monthly releases, Weekly releases, Daily releases. 
20250514_ReleaseManagement (1)


Q: What is a “software release” at CureMD?
A: A package containing a working piece of software that can be deployed to end users.

Q: What server types do live rollouts target?
A: App Servers (CureMD-owned), County Servers (client-owned), and Client Servers (client-owned, accessible over VPN). 
20250514_ReleaseManagement (1)


Q: What is a shipment plan?
A: A schedule that lists which client servers (or counties/apps) receive the release on which dates — used for coordinated rollouts. 
20250514_ReleaseManagement (1)


Q: Who owns deployments for Interfaces?
A: The Interfaces Scrum Team owns Interfaces deployments end-to-end (DevOps/QA-Integration typically not involved). Interfaces often deploy manually due to missing CICD. 
