O. Advanced / tricky questions (for strong impression)
Q: Why does QA-Integration refuse a story that missed the tagging cutoff?
A: To protect release stability — QA-Integration controls the baseline and needs adequate time to audit and test. Including late stories risks insufficient QA and unstable releases.

Q: If an Interfaces piece is high-risk, how would you mitigate deployment risk without CICD?
A: Require thorough manual deployment checklist, rehearse on staging, produce rollback steps, coordinate time window with stakeholders, have DevOps/SCM or Interfaces lead run the manual deploy, and ensure QA-Integration/staging testing before production.

Q: How would you coordinate a release when multiple client servers require different DB scripts?
A: Add per-client setup steps in the release notes, ensure DT contains client-specific scripts and owners, schedule deployments via shipment plan to apply client scripts in the correct order, and verify post-deploy.

Q: What are the consequences of not documenting verification steps in the DT?
A: Poor test coverage, missed regressions, failed deployments, delayed rollouts, and unclear ownership for post-deploy verification — increases downtime and risk.

Q: How do weekly releases differ operationally from monthly releases?
A: Weekly releases are executed for specific client servers that are accessible only weekly (every Thursday) and are prepared/performed by QA-Integration; scrum teams are usually not involved.

